# Akka Provider

The Akka provider lets you manage [Akka platform](https://akka.io) resources — projects, services,
secrets, traffic routes, hostnames, and role bindings — using Terraform.

All operations are performed via the `akka` CLI binary, which must be installed and available in
your `PATH` before you can use this provider.

## Install the akka CLI

```shell
curl -sL https://doc.akka.io/install-cli.sh | bash
```

Verify the installation:

```shell
akka version
```

## Authentication

The provider authenticates with the Akka platform using an API token.

**Recommended**: set the `AKKA_TOKEN` environment variable.

```shell
export AKKA_TOKEN="your-api-token"
```

Alternatively, pass the token directly in the provider block (not recommended for shared configs):

```hcl
provider "akka" {
  organization = "my-org"
  token        = "your-api-token"   # prefer AKKA_TOKEN env var instead
}
```

